Rating: 3
My sister and I made this the day before for Thanksgiving, but accidentally fully cooked the potatoes in the first boiling. Not a problem, though! We drained & cooled, added about 1/3 cup whiskey to the syrup, put all the ingredients together to "marinade", and stored overnight in the fridge. Then we heated it in the oven for the feast. It was delicious, and will grace my Christmas table.

