i've made this every year since pulling it out of the magazine when first published. i use real vermont maple syrup instead of brown sugar, and adjust the cider amount to help compensate for the extra liquid. i use organic foods to make this dish... cider, sweet potatoes, butter, green onions... i believe that this is what creates the fantastic flavor of this dish. and, as with most comfort foods, it's much better the next day. it's requested every thanksgiving!

